1.32	Walter_J._Koladza_Airport	Walter J. Koladza Airport	Walter J. Koladza Airport, , also known as the Great Barrington Airport, is a privately owned airport in Great Barrington, Massachusetts open to the public. It has a single 2,579 ft runway. Walter J. Koladza (died September 1, 2004), a test pilot during World War II, was the owner of the airport for nearly 60 years.	
